Fixed: ASPECT has until now used the normals of the manifold to
apply boundary velocity constraints. This is appropriate in the
majority of cases, but in simulations with mesh deformation,
the manifold coordinate system is not guaranteed to always have
the same normals as the domain boundaries.
This is a problem for tangential velocity boundary conditions.
ASPECT has now been modified to directly calculate normals
using the mesh.
<br>
(Bob Myhill, Rene Gassmoeller and Timo Heister, 2026/01/12)
